events.name: New York Knicks at Charlotte Hornets

headlines.description: — .Jalen Brunson scored 32 points as the New York Knicks extended their winning streak to three games with a 122-108 victory over the Charlotte Hornets on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Brunson scores 32 points, leads Knicks past Hornets for 3rd straight victory

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns broke from a sideline huddle knowing his next shot likely would decide whether the Minnesota Timberwolves escaped New Orleans with a comeback victory or lost their second straight.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns' 29 points and late scoring leads Timberwolves past Pelicans 121-120

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored 23 points and the Chicago Bulls rallied to beat Miami 102-97 on Saturday night, halting the Heat’s winning streak at seven games.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeMar DeRozan scores 23 as Bulls erase 21-point deficit and end Heat's winning streak at 7 games

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo scored 40 points and Damian Lillard added 27 for the Milwaukee Bucks, who extended their winning streak to four games with a 132-125 victory over the Dallas Mavericks on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo scores 40 as Bucks top Mavericks 132-125

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Jaren Jackson Jr. scored 27 points as the short-handed Memphis Grizzlies overcame a 19-point deficit and sent the San Antonio Spurs to their eighth straight loss, 120-108 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jackson's 27 points helps rally short-handed Grizzlies as the Spurs drop their 8th straight game

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — When Golden State's Andrew Wiggins hit a go-ahead 3-pointer with fewer than two seconds remaining in regulation, it seemed to be the difference that the Warriors had been searching for all game long.
headlines.shortLinkText: Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scores 40 as Thunder send Warriors to 6th straight loss, 130-123 in OT
